{
  "stem": "13096.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 1.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am Rachel Hanan.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My maiden name is Rachel Hougnou, and I came from Rhodes Island, an island, very beautiful, in the Dodecanese.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "H-O-U-G-N-O-U.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hanan, H-A-N-A-N.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was born Rhodes Island, now called the Island of Rhodes, on the 22nd of October 1924.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My age now is 71.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father's name was Isaac Hougnou and my mother's name was Perla, maiden, Arlhadeff.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hougnou, H-O-U-G-N-O-U.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother, P-E-R-L-A, Perla.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Arlhadeff, A-R-L-H-A-D-E-F-F.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother was looking after the children because we were eight in the family and she had no time to work outside.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But my father was a tailor, a very good one and very well renowned in the island.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had four brothers and three sisters, two sisters and myself, three girls and four boys.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My eldest brother was named Joseph, and then came Perahia, P-E-R-A-H-I-A.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, Diamante, my sister, my eldest sister.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then it was Aaron, Jack, and [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Fortunae ?] and myself.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very much so.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were very lucky family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were doing everything together, laughing together, crying together, and fighting together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course we had, you know, in that time, you know, it was the fashion, to have-- it was popular to have everybody, you know, all the families, they had 10 children, 9 children, whatever.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we had just relationship with the-- the sisters of my mother, but not with all of the family because otherwise, it was going to be like 100 cousins, and we had no time to-- to see each other.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But only on festival or Rosh Hashanah and Pesach, we used to visit each other and have the meals together.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was like big tables together.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
